      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="660-0251" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Written in the Year 1733.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-660-0251-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">F</hi>Lutt'ring spread thy purple Pinions,Gentle <hi rend="underline">Cupid</hi> o'er my Heart;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-2" rend="align(center)"> I a Slave in thy Dominions;Nature must give Way to Art.II.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="3" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-3" rend="flush left">Mild <hi rend="underline">Arcadians</hi>, ever blooming,Nightly nodding o'er your Flocks,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-4" rend="align(center)"> See my weary Days consuming,All beneath yon flow'ry Rocks.III</l></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l n="5" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-5" rend="flush left">Thus the <hi rend="underline">Cyprian</hi> Goddess weeping,Mourn'd <hi rend="underline">Adonis</hi>, darling Youth:</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-6" rend="align(center)"> Him the Boar in Silence creeping,Gor'd with unrelenting Tooth.IV.</l></lg><lg n="4" type="stanza"><l n="7" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-7" rend="flush left"><hi rend="underline">Cynthia</hi>, tune harmonious Numbers;Fair Discretion string the Lyre;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-8" rend="align(center)"> Sooth my ever-waking Slumbers:Bright <hi rend="underline">Apollo</hi> lend thy Choir.V.</l></lg><lg n="5" type="stanza"><l n="9" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-9" rend="flush left">Gloomy <hi rend="underline">Pluto</hi>, King of Terrors,Arm'd in adamantine Chains,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-10" rend="align(center)"> Lead me to the Chrystal Mirrors,Wat'ring soft <hi rend="underline">Elysian</hi> Plains.VI.</l></lg><lg n="6" type="stanza"><l n="11" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-11" rend="flush left align(center)">Mournful Cypress, verdant Willow,&#13;Gilding my <hi rend="underline">Aurelia</hi>'s Brows,<hi rend="underline">Morpheus</hi> hov'ring o'er my Pillow,Hear me pay my dying Vows.VII.</l></lg><lg n="7" type="stanza"><l n="12" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-12" rend="flush left">Melancholly smooth <hi rend="underline">Meander</hi>,Swiftly purling in a Round,</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-13" rend="align(center)"> On thy Margin Lovers wander,With thy flow'ry Chaplets crown'd.VIII.</l></lg><lg n="8" type="stanza"><l n="14" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-14" rend="flush left">Thus when <hi rend="underline">Philomela</hi> drooping,Softly seeks her silent Mate;</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-660-0251-line-15"> See the Bird of <hi rend="underline">Juno</hi> stooping.Melody resigns to Fate.660-0251   </l></lg></div>
